WEBVTT

00:38.913 --> 00:39.914
What is this place?

00:47.547 --> 00:48.381
What's wrong?

00:48.465 --> 00:49.883
Oh, it's just…

00:50.759 --> 00:51.885
How did we end up here?

00:52.469 --> 00:53.470
We are on a trip.

00:54.512 --> 00:55.346
What?

00:56.389 --> 00:57.432
You're doing it again.

00:58.975 --> 01:00.310
Want to nap some more?

01:46.606 --> 01:47.440
You're awake?

01:48.066 --> 01:48.900
Yes.

01:51.736 --> 01:53.571
Where did you go at this hour?

01:53.655 --> 01:57.367
I went to the convenience store
to get some stuff for breakfast.

02:00.703 --> 02:02.539
You weren't here, so I was worried.

02:02.622 --> 02:04.332
Oh, you should get more sleep.

02:04.999 --> 02:07.085
I'm wide awake now. I'll go wash up.

02:25.103 --> 02:25.937
What's wrong?

02:26.938 --> 02:29.524
You seem a bit tired.
Did you not sleep well?

02:32.485 --> 02:34.237
I just had trouble dozing off.

02:36.406 --> 02:38.825
Get plenty of rest after work today.

02:39.492 --> 02:40.493
I'll do that.

02:42.829 --> 02:44.289
Drink some of this.

02:59.179 --> 03:00.346
What's wrong?

03:05.727 --> 03:06.561
You…

03:07.312 --> 03:08.897
-Who are you?
-Who are you?

03:10.231 --> 03:13.401
You hurt me in a lot of ways.
You don't even recognize me anymore?

03:32.462 --> 03:37.884
Ms. Seo Mi-rae, renew your subscription
to continue your date with Gu Yeong-il.

03:57.403 --> 03:58.988
Are you leaving already?

03:59.572 --> 04:02.825
Yes. I'm going to go home,
then go to work from there.

04:03.493 --> 04:05.578
-I'll see you later, then.
-Okay.

04:08.331 --> 04:09.499
GU YEONG-IL

04:09.582 --> 04:12.043
Why did you leave so fast?
You didn't even say goodbye.

04:12.126 --> 04:12.961
What is this?

04:16.214 --> 04:17.048
What's wrong?

04:19.592 --> 04:20.677
It's just…

04:21.928 --> 04:24.889
You seem a bit tired.
Did you not sleep well?

04:26.766 --> 04:29.018
I just had trouble dozing off.

04:31.062 --> 04:32.397
Last night,

04:33.815 --> 04:35.858
did something happen

04:37.026 --> 04:39.237
while I was asleep?

04:44.534 --> 04:49.455
You were just by yourself
because you couldn't fall asleep, right?

04:58.673 --> 04:59.882
I saw it.

05:02.218 --> 05:03.052
What…

05:03.886 --> 05:04.887
You saw what?

05:06.472 --> 05:07.765
Boyfriend on Demand.

05:12.270 --> 05:15.440
Well, what exactly did you see?

05:17.900 --> 05:19.235
I saw everything.

05:19.861 --> 05:20.862
That man too.

05:32.165 --> 05:33.166
Talk next time?

05:34.375 --> 05:37.879
This isn't… It's not what you think.

05:37.962 --> 05:41.632
So, things ended up this way somehow,
but please don't misunderstand.

05:42.633 --> 05:43.468
Misunderstand?

05:43.551 --> 05:46.054
You and Gu Yeong-il, I mean…

05:46.137 --> 05:49.140
That man has nothing to do with you.

05:50.933 --> 05:52.810
You know Mr. Min, right?

05:52.894 --> 05:55.897
He asked me for some reviews,

05:55.980 --> 06:01.152
so I ended up trying Boyfriend on Demand,
and things happened, and…

06:01.235 --> 06:04.447
I ended up making a character, and he…

06:04.530 --> 06:07.950
A character who looks just like me
was created by coincidence?

06:08.034 --> 06:13.790
I know this may all seem absurd.
I mean, I thought so too.

06:13.873 --> 06:16.459
But it really was a coincidence.

06:18.294 --> 06:20.671
I'm sorry I didn't tell you sooner.

06:21.923 --> 06:25.259
I just kept it from you
because it might sound weird.

06:29.555 --> 06:30.723
All right.

06:33.643 --> 06:34.685
Are you

06:35.603 --> 06:37.105
disappointed in me?

06:41.734 --> 06:43.027
To be honest,

06:44.404 --> 06:46.948
I'm not sure how I'm feeling right now.

06:53.162 --> 06:54.664
I guess I'll know after a while.

07:15.643 --> 07:19.814
I WANTED TO TELL YOU THAT I LIKE YOU

07:26.737 --> 07:27.655
PAYMENT COMPLETE

07:33.494 --> 07:35.037
-Hey, did you--
-Are you okay?

07:35.788 --> 07:36.789
What?

07:38.666 --> 07:40.001
Why did you leave like that?

07:48.759 --> 07:51.345
So you're telling me
he was the one who came to see me?

07:55.141 --> 07:56.976
So nothing happened for real?

07:57.935 --> 07:59.604
-No.
-And you didn't say anything?

08:01.439 --> 08:05.026
What is there to say about us?
You rejecting me was all there was to it.

08:12.783 --> 08:13.868
What was it like?

08:14.660 --> 08:15.578
What do you mean?

08:20.583 --> 08:22.084
When he saw you,

08:23.336 --> 08:24.754
what was his reaction?

08:25.505 --> 08:27.048
Well, he just

08:28.132 --> 08:29.467
acted like he'd seen a ghost.

08:32.053 --> 08:33.638
My good looks must've shocked him.

08:35.181 --> 08:36.349
What am I going to do?

08:38.100 --> 08:39.185
What did that man say?

08:42.855 --> 08:44.190
He doesn't know

08:45.107 --> 08:46.817
how he feels about this.

08:55.034 --> 08:56.118
Damn it.

08:59.163 --> 09:00.665
PRODUCER PARK KYEONG-NAM:
EARLIER…

09:00.748 --> 09:01.832
SO-YEONG

09:04.377 --> 09:06.420
Yes, So-yeong, let me get back to--

09:06.504 --> 09:07.797
Ms. Seo, this is bad!

09:07.880 --> 09:08.798
Huh?

09:19.016 --> 09:22.436
Director Hwang told Ms. Yun
that her contract was terminated.

09:31.070 --> 09:34.657
She needed someone to vent her anger on
and found the perfect target.

09:34.740 --> 09:35.658
Ms. Yun, how can I--

09:35.741 --> 09:36.993
-Move.
-Yes, ma'am.

09:39.870 --> 09:43.332
She said she had nothing more to lose
and stormed out.

09:43.416 --> 09:45.251
-Taxi! Hey!
-Please stop her.

09:51.257 --> 09:52.341
Oh, Yun Song…

09:52.425 --> 09:54.510
Wow, so this is what you've been up to.

09:54.594 --> 09:57.847
That coffee sure smells amazing,
doesn't it?

09:59.098 --> 10:01.017
Goodness, Hermès?

10:01.100 --> 10:03.603
-Wait, that's…
-When did you become so successful?

10:03.686 --> 10:06.272
I'm noticing a lot of things
I haven't seen before.

10:06.355 --> 10:09.150
I'm guessing you must've made a fortune
thanks to someone!

10:09.233 --> 10:12.069
Hey, you can't barge in here like this.
You startled me!

10:12.153 --> 10:13.487
-Mr. Hwang!
-Dear God!

10:13.571 --> 10:16.657
Do you think you're more startled
than someone who got axed?

10:16.741 --> 10:18.492
-Please just put that down.
-What?

10:18.576 --> 10:19.577
What?

10:23.331 --> 10:25.041
Shouldn't have shown off that mug.

10:26.083 --> 10:28.210
-Where is Ms. Yun?
-She's with Mr. Hwang.

10:28.294 --> 10:30.796
-I won't give it to you!
-Hey, have you lost your mind?

10:31.881 --> 10:33.924
-Let go!
-Wait!

10:34.008 --> 10:35.301
Watch the finger!

10:35.801 --> 10:36.969
Let go!

10:38.804 --> 10:40.389
God, my wrist!

10:40.973 --> 10:42.183
It wasn't that bad.

10:45.144 --> 10:47.605
You handle that crap with such care,

10:47.688 --> 10:51.692
but don't care that all that drawing
left me barely able to hold chopsticks.

10:51.776 --> 10:53.944
Are authors less important to you
than a mug?

10:54.445 --> 10:55.613
Huh?

10:55.696 --> 10:57.907
I'll have you know
this is a workplace injury.

10:57.990 --> 11:00.743
Do you have any idea
how much this wrist is worth?

11:05.873 --> 11:07.083
Ms. Yun.

11:10.670 --> 11:14.965
Seo? Where have you been all this time?

11:15.466 --> 11:17.718
Please calm down. We can talk--

11:17.802 --> 11:20.763
I can't put up with this crap anymore.

11:25.643 --> 11:26.894
Let's go.

11:26.977 --> 11:30.064
No need to stick around
with this shitty company any longer.

11:35.277 --> 11:36.320
But…

11:39.615 --> 11:41.701
-You can't just leave like this.
-Let go.

11:41.784 --> 11:43.869
Let's try to convince the director--

11:43.953 --> 11:44.787
Let go!

11:44.870 --> 11:45.830
Ms. Yun, please!

12:18.946 --> 12:23.033
Goodness, that temper of hers.
She really needs to get it under control.

12:29.039 --> 12:31.876
Why are you looking at me?
What's with the grim faces?

12:39.842 --> 12:43.429
EPISODE 10
AN UTTERLY NORMAL FUTURE

12:58.861 --> 13:00.529
I got scratched a little.

13:25.805 --> 13:26.639
There.

13:28.349 --> 13:29.391
Thank you.

13:30.643 --> 13:32.728
Shouldn't you be checking in on Ms. Yun?

13:33.979 --> 13:35.815
Once she calms down a bit.

13:41.987 --> 13:45.866
About what we were talking about
this morning…

13:46.367 --> 13:47.868
You already explained everything.

13:50.913 --> 13:52.164
Are you okay?

13:55.960 --> 13:59.255
Did you see how she pulled
a shoulder throw on Mr. Hwang?

13:59.839 --> 14:01.257
Stop making it a big deal.

14:01.841 --> 14:02.675
What did I do?

14:04.635 --> 14:07.388
What's wrong? Are you hurt? Let me see.

14:07.471 --> 14:08.639
It's nothing.

14:09.223 --> 14:11.392
Look at her face. This won't do.

14:11.475 --> 14:13.894
Let's head out.
What you need is a bowl of unadon.

14:14.478 --> 14:16.063
You're having lunch, aren't you?

14:18.399 --> 14:21.318
I have a meeting with an author later.

14:22.152 --> 14:24.321
Yeah? That's too bad.

14:25.155 --> 14:27.992
Are you treating your teammates
to unadon, then?

14:28.075 --> 14:29.410
Doors opening.

14:42.548 --> 14:43.382
What is it?

14:45.467 --> 14:47.970
I thought we got interrupted earlier.

14:49.972 --> 14:52.057
Are you sure you're okay?

14:54.310 --> 14:55.227
Yes.

15:07.072 --> 15:08.908
Look at me.

15:19.668 --> 15:21.086
You actually made it?

15:28.302 --> 15:29.678
Doors opening.

15:32.890 --> 15:34.475
Well, Hwany

15:36.143 --> 15:37.728
is waiting for me.

15:38.729 --> 15:39.688
I'll be going now.

15:42.066 --> 15:43.651
Okay. Bye.

15:44.944 --> 15:45.778
Right.

15:55.537 --> 15:57.206
I had a strange feeling.

15:58.540 --> 16:03.671
That Park Kyeong-nam had gone back
to the man I once knew him as.

16:05.381 --> 16:06.465
This unease.

16:07.466 --> 16:09.301
Why does it feel so familiar?

16:31.991 --> 16:34.660
What I need to do
is pretend everything's okay.

16:37.037 --> 16:38.163
PRODUCER PARK KYEONG-NAM

16:38.247 --> 16:39.665
Good luck with your meeting.

16:53.554 --> 16:57.766
GOOD LUCK WITH YOUR MEETING!
(UNREAD)

17:02.271 --> 17:03.355
Are you busy?

17:05.024 --> 17:06.191
You like him that much?

17:08.777 --> 17:12.573
When you like someone,
you go all in, no matter what happens.

17:13.115 --> 17:14.033
That's a no-no.

17:15.242 --> 17:16.326
How come?

17:16.410 --> 17:18.746
It's just how relationship dynamics work.

17:18.829 --> 17:22.958
Whoever shows their affection more
ends up getting dragged around in the end.

17:23.042 --> 17:24.793
You're being dramatic.

17:24.877 --> 17:27.713
Think about your past relationships.

17:30.132 --> 17:33.719
Fine, let's say you're right.
What's wrong with getting dragged around?

17:36.055 --> 17:36.889
I mean,

17:36.972 --> 17:40.350
if you're cool with staring into
your phone all day, waiting for a reply,

17:40.434 --> 17:43.729
and going, "Has he lost interest in me?
Is this a one-sided thing?"

17:44.605 --> 17:47.191
while trembling with anxiety,
then it's okay.

17:49.526 --> 17:51.445
Just put a curse on me, will you?

17:51.528 --> 17:54.114
And that's how the vicious cycle goes on.

17:54.740 --> 17:58.327
You get anxious. You get clingy.
He grows distant day by day.

17:58.827 --> 18:00.662
This especially applies to you.

18:00.746 --> 18:03.165
When things get a little awkward
for the first time,

18:03.248 --> 18:06.502
you need to be extra careful.

18:08.712 --> 18:09.713
Why?

18:10.214 --> 18:15.135
That's when it starts to show
which one of you likes the other way more.

18:16.053 --> 18:20.933
That's when the lord and the serf
in the relationship are determined.

18:22.017 --> 18:23.519
Always so dramatic.

18:23.602 --> 18:24.728
ARE YOU BUSY?

18:33.445 --> 18:34.613
You've been moody lately.

18:35.614 --> 18:38.534
The other day, you were grinning.
Today, you look like crap.

18:38.617 --> 18:40.994
What are you talking about?
I'm just eating my food.

18:42.955 --> 18:44.081
Are you busy?

18:46.542 --> 18:47.876
I'm out to eat right--

18:47.960 --> 18:49.419
You're seeing someone, huh?

18:51.547 --> 18:53.966
Want me to guess who? It's too easy.

18:54.716 --> 18:56.426
I can act like I don't know if you want.

18:57.469 --> 18:58.387
What?

18:59.429 --> 19:00.305
You knew?

19:00.973 --> 19:04.476
Man, don't treat me like an NPC.
How could I not know?

19:05.060 --> 19:08.730
I had my suspicions the moment I heard
you were working late every Friday.

19:08.814 --> 19:10.732
You can talk to me about Ms. Seo.

19:10.816 --> 19:13.152
Forget it. I can't talk to you about her.

19:13.235 --> 19:15.779
What's it about?
So there is something going on.

19:22.494 --> 19:23.328
Well…

19:26.290 --> 19:27.541
It's just that…

19:27.624 --> 19:30.377
What? Did she do something to upset you?

19:31.170 --> 19:34.214
No, I wouldn't say that, but…

19:34.298 --> 19:35.132
Are you mad?

19:35.883 --> 19:38.552
-Are you fuming?
-No, it's not that bad.

19:38.635 --> 19:40.179
What then, are you just sulking?

19:41.346 --> 19:42.181
Huh?

19:42.264 --> 19:46.185
I mean, if you're not upset or mad at her,
then you're just sulking.

19:47.853 --> 19:48.687
I'm…

19:49.354 --> 19:51.231
I'm sulking? Me?

19:51.315 --> 19:55.319
Hey, it's nothing to be embarrassed about.
We all get sulky.

19:56.904 --> 19:58.655
No, I've never sulked before.

19:58.739 --> 19:59.698
Is that right?

20:00.199 --> 20:02.451
Sure. Of course you haven't.

20:05.204 --> 20:06.038
Hey.

20:10.751 --> 20:11.835
So…

20:13.879 --> 20:16.715
why do people normally get sulky
with someone?

20:30.145 --> 20:32.064
ARE YOU BUSY?
(READ)

20:32.147 --> 20:33.732
He left me on read?

20:36.193 --> 20:38.195
PRODUCER PARK KYEONG-NAM
CALL

20:39.154 --> 20:42.699
Don't get clingy! Don't call him
just because you're a bit worried!

20:42.783 --> 20:44.868
That's a fast track to a rut, you know.

21:00.259 --> 21:01.843
I'm going to bed now.

21:04.304 --> 21:05.806
What are you so worried about?

21:08.809 --> 21:10.769
It's not like you committed a crime.

21:14.398 --> 21:17.317
As long as nothing happened
between you two, that's fine.

21:19.361 --> 21:20.654
Wait.

21:21.238 --> 21:24.491
If that man ever acts petty, tell me.

21:26.368 --> 21:27.202
What?

21:28.578 --> 21:31.832
Let me know if he frustrates you
or gives you a hard time.

21:33.542 --> 21:34.376
Why?

21:35.377 --> 21:36.628
I'll help you.

21:47.973 --> 21:48.807
Is everything okay?

21:48.890 --> 21:49.725
GU YEONG-IL

21:52.144 --> 21:53.979
Okay. Good night.

22:16.293 --> 22:18.337
OKAY GOOD NIGHT
(READ)

22:20.088 --> 22:22.424
Why do people normally get sulky
with someone?

22:22.507 --> 22:23.759
Because they like them.

22:26.470 --> 22:30.057
Wow. You must really like Ms. Seo.

22:41.276 --> 22:43.528
-Did you have break--
-Did you get some sleep?

22:45.155 --> 22:46.656
I had breakfast.

22:47.741 --> 22:49.242
I got some sleep.

23:05.092 --> 23:06.093
What's going on?

23:06.718 --> 23:08.553
He's acting somewhat cold.

23:14.518 --> 23:16.478
Why is she avoiding my eyes?

23:19.940 --> 23:20.857
I'll…

23:22.901 --> 23:24.319
get going now.

23:25.112 --> 23:26.238
Okay.

23:45.298 --> 23:46.466
BOYFRIEND ON DEMAND

23:47.551 --> 23:49.845
-Isn't that Yun Song?
-Yeah, that's her.

23:52.222 --> 23:54.015
Are you here for the Karrot trade?

23:54.099 --> 23:55.308
Oh, yes, Karrot.

23:59.980 --> 24:01.148
Did you format this?

24:01.231 --> 24:02.274
No.

24:02.357 --> 24:03.650
Can you do it right now?

24:08.780 --> 24:12.200
You've got such a kind heart, Song.

24:14.244 --> 24:16.121
I should help you get motivated.

24:22.711 --> 24:25.130
If it's too much trouble,
I can do it later.

24:25.213 --> 24:27.632
I'll wire you the money.
What's your account…

24:33.096 --> 24:34.681
Hello?

24:36.808 --> 24:38.643
What the heck? Are you not selling it?

24:45.734 --> 24:46.693
I'm sorry.

24:55.285 --> 24:57.370
This is driving me crazy.

25:08.048 --> 25:10.091
-Hey.
-What are you up to now?

25:10.175 --> 25:12.344
You said
you've lost your appetite recently,

25:12.427 --> 25:13.970
so I'm going to make you soup.

25:16.264 --> 25:17.891
Are you trying to drive me crazy?

25:17.974 --> 25:20.519
Why carrot soup, of all things?

25:21.186 --> 25:22.687
What's wrong? It's what you like.

25:22.771 --> 25:24.981
You almost got karroted off.
You know that?

25:25.607 --> 25:27.025
Did I do something wrong?

25:27.108 --> 25:28.777
Yes, you did!

25:28.860 --> 25:32.656
I didn't have to know any of this,
but you made me find out.

25:32.739 --> 25:35.200
You're the reason I ended up like this.

25:35.784 --> 25:39.788
Hey, stop lashing out at me
and tell me what this is about.

25:41.248 --> 25:42.249
I don't know.

25:43.250 --> 25:46.628
Everyone keeps mocking me for liking you.

25:49.130 --> 25:49.965
Mocking you?

25:51.675 --> 25:52.509
Who is?

25:53.385 --> 25:56.555
They are saying
things won't work out between us.

25:57.806 --> 25:59.182
Who said that?

26:00.183 --> 26:03.895
Everyone except you and me. All of them!

26:05.480 --> 26:06.314
Come here.

26:10.068 --> 26:10.902
It's okay.

26:11.736 --> 26:12.571
It's okay.

26:15.657 --> 26:16.575
Here.

26:19.452 --> 26:20.787
-You like?
-Yeah.

26:22.539 --> 26:24.124
Why do you like me?

26:24.708 --> 26:27.794
You only like me
because you have to, don't you?

26:30.463 --> 26:31.715
Why do you like me?

26:32.882 --> 26:34.050
You're good-looking.

26:34.676 --> 26:37.345
You're a good cook. You're nice to me.

26:37.429 --> 26:40.223
You're cute, and you're kind.

26:42.017 --> 26:46.855
-Then why are you being like this to me?
-You might have a hundred good qualities.

26:47.355 --> 26:49.941
But you have one fatal flaw.

26:50.025 --> 26:52.027
I didn't ask about my pros and cons.

26:52.736 --> 26:55.488
I asked why you're being like this to me.
Do you hate me now?

26:57.407 --> 26:59.034
Then what's the issue?

27:01.286 --> 27:05.123
I asked you first. Answer me.
Tell me why you like me.

27:10.211 --> 27:11.046
I just

27:12.756 --> 27:14.466
like it when you're happy.

27:15.634 --> 27:17.135
There's no other reason.

27:17.886 --> 27:21.473
That's not what I'm asking.
What do you like about me?

27:21.556 --> 27:22.807
Why do you like me?

27:22.891 --> 27:24.643
Liking you

27:25.894 --> 27:27.729
and liking you being happy,

27:28.647 --> 27:29.731
are they different?

27:30.398 --> 27:33.318
I'd be okay with it
even if you had 10,000 flaws.

27:34.069 --> 27:35.153
But

27:35.236 --> 27:39.199
if you absolutely can't stand my one flaw…

27:41.743 --> 27:42.869
then you can leave.

27:45.080 --> 27:46.081
Because

27:46.790 --> 27:49.125
your happiness is what matters to me most.

28:05.058 --> 28:06.393
Did I give you such a hard time?

28:08.353 --> 28:11.690
It's not because of you.
It's because of me.

28:12.190 --> 28:16.111
Who cares how others think about me
when I like you so much?

28:16.611 --> 28:19.698
I'll stop going on Karrot.
I'm done with that now.

28:20.949 --> 28:22.992
What's this Karrot you keep mentioning?

28:24.869 --> 28:26.037
You don't need to know.

28:27.831 --> 28:29.249
Eat the soup first.

28:29.332 --> 28:32.335
It's going to get cold. You seemed hungry.

28:33.545 --> 28:34.963
-Is it good?
-Yes.

28:35.046 --> 28:36.214
It's good, huh?

28:37.006 --> 28:38.550
-Yum yum.
-Yum yum, nom nom.

28:38.633 --> 28:40.343
Yum yum, nom nom. Here.

28:44.305 --> 28:45.473
There.

28:46.391 --> 28:47.809
I put away all my mugs.

28:48.393 --> 28:49.978
She might barge in again any day.

28:50.520 --> 28:54.190
We can't let our guard down
until Yun Song has calmed down.

28:54.274 --> 28:58.319
Sir, how could you do that
without even giving me a heads-up?

28:58.403 --> 29:02.574
Hey, I only did that to save you
from the trouble of telling her yourself.

29:02.657 --> 29:03.908
God, I'm hurt.

29:03.992 --> 29:07.996
Even Mr. Min said he didn't want
to make an issue out of the plagiarism,

29:08.079 --> 29:09.998
and the rest is just a private matter.

29:10.081 --> 29:11.833
Did she commit a sin or something?

29:11.916 --> 29:15.420
Until the public unrest dies down,
put her work on hold,

29:15.920 --> 29:18.339
and focus on managing the other authors.

29:18.423 --> 29:20.759
Putting her on hiatus would be inevitable,

29:21.760 --> 29:24.012
but I don't agree
with terminating her contract.

29:24.095 --> 29:25.013
Oh, that's right.

29:26.014 --> 29:28.933
You're my boss.
Oh my, it totally slipped my mind!

29:29.017 --> 29:30.059
Mr. Hwang!

29:38.651 --> 29:40.236
Fine, then.

29:40.320 --> 29:43.406
I'll reconsider it.
Put her on hiatus for now.

29:44.449 --> 29:46.117
But I can't promise you anything.

29:46.618 --> 29:50.163
Now please leave, ma'am.
You're making me very uncomfortable.

30:09.808 --> 30:10.642
Going somewhere?

30:12.101 --> 30:14.020
I need some air.
I'm going to work outside.

30:32.872 --> 30:34.624
Why are you here by yourself?

30:36.334 --> 30:38.253
Oh, everyone else went home.

30:38.920 --> 30:39.838
They all went home?

30:39.921 --> 30:44.259
Yun Song's series has been put on hold,
so Mi-rae's back to leaving work on time.

30:44.926 --> 30:47.595
Only the team leader remains
to hold down the fort.

30:48.596 --> 30:50.014
The nerve of those punks.

30:50.098 --> 30:52.725
They've never once told me
they were leaving before…

30:57.272 --> 30:58.147
You too?

31:03.570 --> 31:05.071
Huh? You didn't go home?

31:05.154 --> 31:07.323
No. I was working outside.

31:08.157 --> 31:10.660
Wait, everyone went home?
Are you here by yourself?

31:10.743 --> 31:12.912
Mm-hmm. They all left a while ago.

31:13.872 --> 31:18.126
I haven't said anything to you guys,
but I have a lot pent up inside.

31:18.209 --> 31:22.130
I never talk about it,
but now that you're here, Mi-rae…

31:36.728 --> 31:40.732
For the first time since we got together,
he left work without even telling me.

31:41.399 --> 31:42.734
What does this mean?

31:46.529 --> 31:47.864
-I'M OFF TO A MEETING.
-OKAY.

31:47.947 --> 31:49.532
HEADING BACK NOW
WANT SOME COOKIES?

31:49.616 --> 31:50.450
I'M GOOD

31:50.533 --> 31:52.869
-WHEN DOES YOUR MEETING END?
-IT JUST ENDED

31:52.952 --> 31:54.871
-THAT WAS LONG, YOU SHOULD EAT LUNCH
-OKAY

32:06.841 --> 32:08.676
She left work without even telling me?

32:14.182 --> 32:15.350
He's changed.

32:16.100 --> 32:19.854
Ever since he found out about
Boyfriend on Demand, he's changed.

32:35.286 --> 32:37.246
She left first and didn't even text me.

32:47.131 --> 32:49.217
WOULD YOU LIKE TO CANCEL
YOUR SUBSCRIPTION?

32:49.801 --> 32:52.303
I'll help you patch things up
with that guy.

33:12.490 --> 33:13.324
Back so soon?

33:16.619 --> 33:17.453
Want a drink?

33:23.334 --> 33:24.419
What's the problem?

33:25.962 --> 33:27.922
Tell me what's troubling you the most.

33:29.549 --> 33:30.550
I just

33:31.759 --> 33:33.845
don't know what he's thinking.

33:34.804 --> 33:37.807
Besides, I keep obsessing over
every little thing about him.

33:38.391 --> 33:41.227
I'm glued to my phone all the time,
wondering when he'll reply.

33:41.894 --> 33:43.938
It feels as though
my life has disappeared.

33:44.689 --> 33:46.107
Why not just ask what he's thinking?

33:48.234 --> 33:50.737
I can't bring myself to do that.

33:51.821 --> 33:53.740
And you don't want to break up like this?

33:59.454 --> 34:04.208
So, you feel that he has changed
after he found me, but you can't ask him.

34:05.168 --> 34:08.087
At the same time, doing nothing
makes you nervous and frustrated.

34:08.671 --> 34:09.505
Is that it?

34:11.299 --> 34:12.216
Yes.

34:12.800 --> 34:15.303
Then we'll have to find out
how he feels about you.

34:17.263 --> 34:18.139
But how?

34:24.896 --> 34:26.355
Let's go somewhere else.

34:39.535 --> 34:40.578
Seo Mi-rae.

35:02.391 --> 35:03.226
What is this?

35:04.185 --> 35:05.019
Are you surprised?

35:06.187 --> 35:09.524
Why are we at a place like this?
And what's with that outfit?

35:13.986 --> 35:15.696
Did I make your heart flutter?

35:20.868 --> 35:23.955
I won't get the wrong idea.
I know full well that you like that man.

35:26.249 --> 35:29.418
Isn't it confusing when the familiar
gets mixed up with the unfamiliar?

35:30.419 --> 35:35.341
In an unexpected situation like this,
people tend to reveal their true feelings.

35:35.424 --> 35:36.759
The heart cannot lie.

35:38.636 --> 35:40.555
Can you make it make sense?

35:42.723 --> 35:46.477
Well, I'm proposing that we create
a situation that he won't expect.

35:48.396 --> 35:52.233
Then, we'll be able to confirm
whether his heart still beats for you.

35:57.655 --> 36:01.075
Show up at a familiar location,
but in a getup that he's unfamiliar with.

36:06.873 --> 36:08.166
Hello.

36:09.083 --> 36:10.334
-You look so pretty!
-Hi.

36:11.544 --> 36:12.628
-Hello.
-What?

36:13.379 --> 36:14.839
-She's wearing a skirt!
-What?

36:14.922 --> 36:16.549
You look so pretty today.

36:17.133 --> 36:18.009
Really!

36:21.888 --> 36:23.139
Ms. Seo!

36:23.222 --> 36:24.473
Good morning.

36:24.557 --> 36:26.100
What's this?

36:26.184 --> 36:28.352
What's going on?
Are you also being interviewed?

36:29.228 --> 36:30.062
Interviewed?

36:31.898 --> 36:33.983
I hope the trip here
wasn't too inconvenient.

36:34.066 --> 36:36.319
I hope our article
didn't inconvenience you.

36:36.402 --> 36:38.321
Oh well, I don't mind such things.

36:38.404 --> 36:40.531
Webtoons Monthly is here for an interview.

36:41.741 --> 36:44.911
All the recent articles are about Ms. Yun,

36:45.411 --> 36:49.248
but the contest awards ceremony
and the new releases are coming up.

36:49.832 --> 36:51.334
He's on a full charm offensive.

36:51.417 --> 36:52.835
Please take good care of us.

36:52.919 --> 36:54.587
Why isn't he here yet?

36:55.254 --> 36:56.088
Who?

36:57.173 --> 36:58.758
They're here for Mr. Hwang and--

36:58.841 --> 37:00.092
Hey, Kyeong-nam!

37:05.806 --> 37:06.807
No way.

37:12.688 --> 37:13.522
Holy crap.

37:22.114 --> 37:23.282
Hello.

37:24.158 --> 37:26.077
Hey! Can you hurry up, please?

37:26.160 --> 37:28.663
-Yes, sir.
-They're waiting for you, Mr. Park.

37:31.082 --> 37:32.083
Are you okay?

37:32.833 --> 37:34.502
Yeah, I'm fine.

37:37.004 --> 37:39.090
Why did she have to look so pretty today?

37:39.840 --> 37:41.008
So much for confirming!

37:41.092 --> 37:43.803
It only confirmed
that my heart's still alive and well.

37:44.595 --> 37:48.015
Man, he's good.
I wasn't expecting a countermove.

37:49.183 --> 37:51.352
I spent all that money at the salon
for nothing.

37:52.144 --> 37:53.729
This won't do. Change of plans.

37:54.605 --> 37:57.942
Before we confirm his heart,
let's manage yours first.

38:01.821 --> 38:02.947
Leave your heart here.

38:05.324 --> 38:07.910
Like the Tin Man
who was missing his heart.

38:07.994 --> 38:10.746
Step into the mindset
of someone living without a heart.

38:12.039 --> 38:14.875
I'm sure you'll feel a lot more relaxed
once you have no heart.

39:00.588 --> 39:01.839
Stay put at home.

39:16.896 --> 39:19.648
My heart isn't here.

39:19.732 --> 39:22.234
-A bug! On your back!
-What? Me?

39:22.318 --> 39:24.904
Oh God, get it off! Get it off me, please!

39:25.488 --> 39:26.906
That's why today…

39:27.406 --> 39:28.657
Please!

39:31.285 --> 39:33.788
What was it? Goodness, that's creepy.

39:34.497 --> 39:35.331
It's nothing.

39:38.542 --> 39:41.545
…I won't lose my cool,
no matter what happens.

39:46.467 --> 39:48.844
She grabbed a bug with her bare hands?

39:58.813 --> 40:00.898
I'm sorry. The meeting ended a bit late.

40:00.981 --> 40:01.899
Oh, it's fine.

40:01.982 --> 40:03.234
Sorry about that.

40:09.615 --> 40:11.575
CUSTOM-TAILORED BOYFRIEND GU YEONG-IL

40:14.328 --> 40:15.162
Mr. Min,

40:15.913 --> 40:17.748
what is that?

40:18.457 --> 40:20.876
-Excuse me?
-Oh, I meant Gu Yeong-il.

40:21.961 --> 40:23.170
Oh, this?

40:23.254 --> 40:26.924
It was developed as a special bonus
for the users who didn't like our themes

40:27.007 --> 40:28.676
because they were too contrived,

40:28.759 --> 40:31.846
but it's gotten so popular
that we have a dedicated team for it now.

40:32.888 --> 40:35.391
If it's custom-tailored,
does it cover everything?

40:35.975 --> 40:39.103
We try to make it as close
to the user's ideal man as possible.

40:39.186 --> 40:40.855
Personality, looks, everything.

40:41.439 --> 40:44.650
Whoa, then he must be a perfect man.

40:44.733 --> 40:49.196
Some say that he's definitely
a cut above a human boyfriend.

40:49.280 --> 40:51.949
But as it turns out,
that wasn't the case for some.

40:54.326 --> 40:55.327
Why not?

40:56.412 --> 40:59.832
Aren't movies more fun
when you don't know the ending?

41:00.416 --> 41:05.045
The man of your dreams has appeared,
but you already know he will like you,

41:05.129 --> 41:07.965
and that breaks the immersion
for some people.

41:09.216 --> 41:12.136
Besides, love is about
giving your heart to someone

41:12.219 --> 41:14.722
when you have no idea what will come next.

41:15.890 --> 41:19.059
And it's not like
love can simply be mimicked.

41:19.560 --> 41:20.686
That's the hardest part.

41:23.189 --> 41:24.190
True that!

41:26.192 --> 41:29.236
With TMTK gone, it feels like a free win,
and I don't love that.

41:30.946 --> 41:33.449
But has it really been canceled?
It hasn't, right?

41:33.532 --> 41:35.117
I don't know much about it.

41:35.868 --> 41:39.705
Setting the second male lead aside,
there's still so much left to wrap up.

41:39.788 --> 41:42.500
There's the aunt's embezzlement
during the Cebu construction

41:42.583 --> 41:45.377
and the affair between the chairman
and Director Song.

41:45.878 --> 41:47.963
When does she plan on revealing all that?

41:48.047 --> 41:50.966
Try talking to Ms. Yun.
You're a fan, so she might tell you.

41:51.050 --> 41:52.176
A fan?

41:52.718 --> 41:53.636
Are you insane?

41:53.719 --> 41:57.765
I only read it to review the coloring work
So-yeong poured her heart and soul into.

42:00.809 --> 42:04.146
About that thing earlier on…
Gu Yeong-il, was it?

42:05.314 --> 42:07.399
Do you think So-yeong might have made one?

42:07.483 --> 42:11.195
I'm a little curious as to
what her Gu Yeong-il would look like.

42:13.030 --> 42:13.864
Well…

42:15.574 --> 42:18.327
how do you think you'd feel
if he looked like you?

42:18.410 --> 42:19.495
Me?

42:24.750 --> 42:26.418
Come on, man!

42:26.502 --> 42:29.672
I'd love it, of course!
That would mean I'm the man of her dreams.

42:31.131 --> 42:32.299
Hold on a second.

42:32.800 --> 42:37.471
He would only look like me
and be better than me in every other way.

42:37.555 --> 42:38.806
Should I be worried?

42:39.765 --> 42:42.935
Nah, I shouldn't be. I can beat him.

42:46.188 --> 42:50.401
Because I like her more. That jerk
would only be pretending to like her.

42:51.652 --> 42:55.114
How would that jerk know
how pretty and adorable So-yeong is?

42:56.156 --> 42:58.826
Damn, talking about her
makes me miss her more.

43:07.376 --> 43:09.461
-Hwany, I'm sorry.
-Huh?

43:51.045 --> 43:52.546
I thought you left for the day.

43:54.089 --> 43:56.925
Mi-rae just went to get us some snacks.
You're missing out.

43:57.009 --> 43:58.594
Where did she go?

43:59.803 --> 44:01.096
The café right out front.

44:44.473 --> 44:45.808
Huh? What?

44:46.433 --> 44:47.518
Why…

44:47.601 --> 44:48.977
Did you run all the way here?

44:50.854 --> 44:51.689
I just

44:52.648 --> 44:54.149
wanted to follow my heart.

44:55.025 --> 44:56.110
What?

44:57.111 --> 44:58.779
To see you when I want to see you…

45:00.823 --> 45:02.574
and hug you when I want to hug you.

45:11.625 --> 45:12.710
Should I not do that?

45:14.670 --> 45:15.587
Well…

45:39.403 --> 45:40.237
Do it.

45:41.739 --> 45:44.408
That's what I want to do too.

46:17.232 --> 46:18.400
Are you sure about this?

46:18.484 --> 46:22.279
There's no better person
to help us strengthen our scenarios.

46:22.362 --> 46:24.031
I don't know about this.

46:24.114 --> 46:27.951
She probably stays at home all day
watching dating shows and playing games.

46:29.536 --> 46:32.247
I doubt she'll be capable of
communicating with us.

46:59.399 --> 47:00.901
Boyfriend on Demand?

47:02.361 --> 47:03.195
Yes.

47:04.029 --> 47:05.948
I am Boyfriend on Demand.

47:07.533 --> 47:09.952
This is a special case for us, too,

47:10.536 --> 47:14.206
but we were really impressed
by your analysis of our themes.

47:14.289 --> 47:15.791
That's why we reached out.

47:16.834 --> 47:17.835
Ji-yeon,

47:19.169 --> 47:20.420
what is your dream?

47:20.504 --> 47:24.967
I'd like to review all 900 boyfriends,
then publish a book about that, and so on.

47:26.260 --> 47:28.178
You plan on meeting all 900 of them?

47:28.262 --> 47:30.264
Yes. I'm almost there.

47:30.848 --> 47:32.266
Then you won't live your life?

47:34.309 --> 47:35.769
What I mean to say is…

47:38.313 --> 47:40.148
I'm living my life to the fullest.

47:40.232 --> 47:44.194
You must have thought Boyfriend on Demand
is all I do. Not at all.

47:44.278 --> 47:47.364
Then do you have other hobbies?

47:47.948 --> 47:49.116
My hobbies?

47:51.034 --> 47:52.202
Going on dates?

47:56.456 --> 47:57.541
Ji-yeon!

47:59.167 --> 48:00.252
Yes?

48:00.961 --> 48:02.629
I didn't get to give you my card.

48:07.843 --> 48:08.677
Thank you.

48:11.388 --> 48:12.514
Have a safe trip home.

48:12.598 --> 48:13.974
-Goodbye.
-Right.

48:20.147 --> 48:21.899
Didn't see the step there.

48:22.774 --> 48:23.942
I'm okay.

48:24.902 --> 48:26.153
-Goodbye.
-Bye.

48:30.449 --> 48:32.242
I do look pretty good today.

48:40.250 --> 48:41.668
What's your name?

48:41.752 --> 48:43.253
-Hwang Ji-eun.
-Have you arrived?

48:43.754 --> 48:44.588
Right this way.

48:44.671 --> 48:46.673
Did you park on the ground floor?

48:49.009 --> 48:50.052
Just a second!

48:50.552 --> 48:51.762
Where should I put this?

48:51.845 --> 48:53.430
-Put it there, please.
-Sure.

48:56.767 --> 48:58.769
Family members can sit here.

48:58.852 --> 49:02.022
The awardees have designated seats,
so please sit in the front.

49:02.105 --> 49:03.941
Seo Mi-rae, come over here.

49:04.858 --> 49:07.694
Say hello.
The winner of the Best Romantasy Award.

49:07.778 --> 49:10.197
Oh, hello. I loved reading your webtoon.

49:10.280 --> 49:11.531
Thank you.

49:11.615 --> 49:14.534
Producer Seo here
will be managing you from now on.

49:14.618 --> 49:18.705
You know, Yun Song's career took off
because she met this one.

49:19.289 --> 49:21.833
-Glad to be working with you.
-The feeling's mutual.

49:21.917 --> 49:23.168
I'll leave you two to talk.

49:23.251 --> 49:24.628
-Come back later.
-Okay.

49:39.101 --> 49:40.268
It's so hectic.

49:40.352 --> 49:42.229
Did you say hello to the author?

49:42.312 --> 49:45.691
Yes. I read her work so many times
that she didn't feel like a stranger.

49:46.274 --> 49:47.567
I'm proud of myself too.

49:49.569 --> 49:52.489
It'd be nice to judge together again
next year, right?

49:53.490 --> 49:55.117
We might have a fight every day.

49:57.869 --> 49:59.037
Put those scary eyes away.

50:00.497 --> 50:02.165
Hey, what if someone walks in on us?

50:02.249 --> 50:04.543
Wait. This is it.

50:05.168 --> 50:06.962
-The storage room situation.
-Huh?

50:07.754 --> 50:11.174
There's always this kind of scene
in every office romance series.

50:11.675 --> 50:12.843
In the storage room,

50:13.427 --> 50:14.511
just the two of us.

50:17.139 --> 50:20.058
-Stop messing with me.
-Do you hate getting caught that much?

50:22.436 --> 50:24.271
Just not at work.

50:24.855 --> 50:25.689
Why?

50:26.523 --> 50:27.607
Do I embarrass you?

50:29.985 --> 50:31.570
Kyeong-nam, are the picket signs…

50:40.287 --> 50:42.080
Kyeong-nam! Are you okay?

50:42.164 --> 50:44.624
I knew it. Something felt off.

50:45.584 --> 50:48.211
I should've known
my love life wouldn't end happily.

50:48.295 --> 50:49.463
-Is he badly hurt?
-Here!

50:51.048 --> 50:52.716
-Dong-min, go with him.
-Careful.

50:52.799 --> 50:54.676
-Take care.
-I'll go with him.

50:57.095 --> 50:59.598
What was that?
I mean, how did this happen?

50:59.681 --> 51:01.516
What landed on him exactly?

51:02.100 --> 51:03.477
-Mi-rae.
-Ms. Seo!

51:03.560 --> 51:04.603
Mi-rae!

51:18.533 --> 51:19.367
Hey, you there.

51:20.035 --> 51:22.120
Get out of the way. Move aside.

51:22.621 --> 51:24.456
Why are you getting in the way?

51:24.539 --> 51:25.832
Come on, move!

51:25.916 --> 51:27.501
Unbelievable. Sheesh.

51:32.172 --> 51:33.173
Seo Mi-rae?

51:33.924 --> 51:35.008
What's wrong?

51:47.437 --> 51:50.023
Are you okay? It hurts a lot, doesn't it?

51:50.732 --> 51:52.109
What's going on with you two?

51:55.904 --> 51:56.738
What the hell?

51:57.447 --> 51:58.281
No way!

52:00.575 --> 52:02.994
If this is what I think it is,

52:03.078 --> 52:04.663
I should probably leave, huh?

52:05.455 --> 52:06.790
Are you okay?

52:07.916 --> 52:09.543
Well…

52:10.585 --> 52:11.419
Okay. I'll go.

52:11.503 --> 52:13.255
-Thank you.
-Yeah, sure.

52:13.839 --> 52:16.424
I'll keep it secret.
But you have to tell me all about it.

52:16.508 --> 52:18.927
You have to, okay? You have to!

52:19.719 --> 52:20.720
Does it hurt a lot?

52:22.639 --> 52:23.473
I'm fine.

52:32.274 --> 52:34.609
Why did you come?
You should have stayed there.

52:35.652 --> 52:36.987
You got hurt because of me.

52:37.612 --> 52:38.864
It was just an accident.

52:39.573 --> 52:40.407
No.

52:44.202 --> 52:45.787
I pushed you.

52:47.122 --> 52:51.459
I thought something bad might happen
if people were to find out about us.

52:52.919 --> 52:54.504
I did it because I was scared.

52:55.172 --> 52:56.256
I'm sorry.

52:57.799 --> 52:58.633
And

52:59.634 --> 53:01.720
there's something else I didn't tell you.

53:03.555 --> 53:05.891
After you found out
about Boyfriend on Demand,

53:07.392 --> 53:09.895
I went back to Gu Yeong-il.

53:13.565 --> 53:14.399
Why?

53:15.275 --> 53:18.445
At first, I wanted to hear
what the two of you had talked about,

53:19.571 --> 53:20.906
and after that…

53:23.366 --> 53:26.786
it was because I was scared
of how much I liked you.

53:29.456 --> 53:30.874
I thought if I liked you too much,

53:32.792 --> 53:34.461
I might struggle with it later on.

53:38.798 --> 53:41.301
Why do you keep thinking about the end?

53:43.678 --> 53:45.180
Because I'm pathetic.

53:48.308 --> 53:49.142
Right.

53:52.062 --> 53:53.855
But I'm pathetic too.

53:56.149 --> 53:58.318
When I saw Gu Yeong-il for the first time,

53:58.401 --> 54:02.113
the first thing that came to mind was,
"Did she like him before she liked me?"

54:02.614 --> 54:07.619
I wanted to grab him and ask him
about everything from start to finish,

54:08.161 --> 54:10.163
but I couldn't because of my pride.

54:12.707 --> 54:13.708
About that--

54:13.792 --> 54:15.210
But it doesn't matter anymore.

54:15.710 --> 54:17.963
I'm the one you like, after all,

54:18.672 --> 54:19.839
however it started out.

54:24.678 --> 54:26.429
I also get scared every day

54:27.847 --> 54:30.141
of how I keep falling for you
more and more.

54:31.851 --> 54:32.852
But what can I do?

54:35.021 --> 54:37.607
You ran all the way here for me
with a runny nose.

54:38.191 --> 54:39.526
How could I not like you?

54:51.913 --> 54:53.039
Easy.

54:53.123 --> 54:54.249
I'm sorry.

54:58.545 --> 54:59.921
Can't we just

55:00.922 --> 55:04.092
live in the moment and nothing else?

55:07.304 --> 55:10.557
Those who don't doubt the future
and focus on the love in front of them.

55:11.141 --> 55:12.517
That's who I draw.

55:20.400 --> 55:21.609
I'll do that.

55:37.000 --> 55:39.044
All of you,
just come with me to the States.

55:39.127 --> 55:41.087
Who am I gonna have team dinners with now?

55:41.171 --> 55:42.881
-Delicious?
-I'll miss you, sir!

55:43.882 --> 55:47.135
Oh, that's right.
I have to check this before I leave.

55:47.218 --> 55:49.888
I heard something strange recently, okay?

55:49.971 --> 55:53.308
I heard that Seo Mi-rae over there
and Park Kyeong-nam

55:54.142 --> 55:55.435
are dating.

56:03.860 --> 56:05.403
-Yes, we--
-We--

56:17.457 --> 56:19.084
That's ridiculous!

56:19.584 --> 56:22.337
See? They're not dating, you bastard.

56:22.420 --> 56:25.006
Choi Dong-min, you bastard.
You totally played me.

56:25.090 --> 56:27.467
Those two hate each other's guts, man.

56:27.550 --> 56:30.095
Hey, you guys,
let me say this one thing before I leave.

56:30.178 --> 56:32.764
Don't talk behind the authors' backs
too much.

56:32.847 --> 56:34.766
It's like shooting yourself in the foot.

56:34.849 --> 56:36.935
The authors' success is our success.

56:37.018 --> 56:39.646
-Over there!
-Let me drop some words of wisdom.

56:39.729 --> 56:42.273
-Hi. Mind if we join you?
-Sure, you--

56:42.357 --> 56:43.191
Hello!

56:43.274 --> 56:44.275
-Hello.
-Hi.

56:44.359 --> 56:45.193
Yun Song?

56:45.276 --> 56:47.070
What? Am I not allowed here?

56:47.153 --> 56:49.614
No, it's not that. I…

56:50.490 --> 56:51.991
Just take this.

56:52.492 --> 56:55.829
What could this be? What is…

56:55.912 --> 56:58.206
Wait, could this be…

56:59.749 --> 57:01.251
Wow, Yun Song!

57:02.293 --> 57:04.295
Naemo's favorite author!

57:05.380 --> 57:07.632
-You feel me, don't you?
-Sheesh.

57:07.715 --> 57:10.260
-Don't cry. I might leave.
-Oh my God!

57:11.010 --> 57:11.928
Make room, guys.

57:12.011 --> 57:13.805
-Take a seat.
-Come over here.

57:13.888 --> 57:15.181
-Sit.
-I want to drink from this.

57:15.265 --> 57:17.350
-Set her place.
-Wow, this is authentic.

57:17.434 --> 57:18.935
-It's precious.
-Looks amazing.

57:19.018 --> 57:21.521
Don't let them touch. Be careful.

57:24.107 --> 57:25.442
-So well-made.
-Look at him.

57:25.525 --> 57:27.527
-We have to drink to this.
-Cheers!

57:27.610 --> 57:29.070
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

57:29.154 --> 57:30.321
Air cheers.

57:37.120 --> 57:39.539
Hey, it looks like
you're a better drinker now.

57:39.622 --> 57:40.540
Me?

57:40.623 --> 57:42.375
I've been working out lately.

57:42.459 --> 57:46.212
I go to the gym early in the morning
and hit the climber for 30 minutes.

57:46.296 --> 57:49.090
All that exercise
must've given me a brand-new liver.

57:49.174 --> 57:50.717
I feel invincible now.

57:51.217 --> 57:52.135
What motivated you?

57:52.218 --> 57:53.595
Whoa, hold on!

57:54.095 --> 57:56.097
-I'll pick it up.
-I didn't give up.

57:56.181 --> 57:57.807
-Why?
-What was that?

57:59.559 --> 58:00.393
Well…

58:01.436 --> 58:03.354
Here. Use a new one.

58:03.855 --> 58:05.190
Okay. Thank you.

58:09.694 --> 58:12.030
May our longing

58:12.614 --> 58:15.867
One day bring us together

58:16.367 --> 58:18.953
Mr. Hwang!

58:19.037 --> 58:20.663
-Don't go!
-What are you doing?

58:20.747 --> 58:22.582
-We can't live without you.
-Wait!

58:22.665 --> 58:24.542
I'll be back later this year.

58:24.626 --> 58:27.086
So don't ignore my calls,
or you'll pay the price.

58:27.170 --> 58:30.006
-Really? You'll be coming back?
-Of course. I'll be back.

58:30.089 --> 58:31.883
-Don't forget about us!
-I won't!

58:31.966 --> 58:34.677
-Have a safe trip.
-And take care of your health.

58:34.761 --> 58:36.012
I'm gonna miss you.

58:36.095 --> 58:38.765
Try to cut down on the coffee
while you're at it.

58:38.848 --> 58:40.183
God, Yun!

58:40.266 --> 58:43.436
Seeing how much you care about me
makes my leaving feel so real.

58:44.270 --> 58:46.105
How much is this thing anyway?

58:47.524 --> 58:49.234
Hey, let's have a drink!

58:51.027 --> 58:52.612
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

58:52.695 --> 58:54.030
-Love you!
-Love you all!

58:54.113 --> 58:56.407
Hey, the company card's been unleashed!

59:10.797 --> 59:15.134
Maybe goodbyes aren't as bad as we think.

59:49.085 --> 59:50.253
It's been a while.

59:56.301 --> 59:57.343
It has.

59:59.053 --> 01:00:01.556
If it took you this long to come find me,

01:00:01.639 --> 01:00:04.559
it must've gone really well
or really badly, huh?

01:00:06.519 --> 01:00:07.353
Did it go badly?

01:00:12.692 --> 01:00:14.027
Man, that's a shame.

01:00:18.615 --> 01:00:19.782
Are you gonna be okay?

01:00:21.034 --> 01:00:24.203
You might end up lonelier and more anxious
than when you were alone.

01:00:25.163 --> 01:00:27.999
And neither one of your feelings
will stay the same forever.

01:00:30.460 --> 01:00:31.711
That just might be.

01:00:32.795 --> 01:00:33.921
You're okay with that?

01:00:36.424 --> 01:00:37.258
I am.

01:00:38.509 --> 01:00:39.427
Why's that?

01:00:40.762 --> 01:00:42.430
That's just how people are.

01:00:42.513 --> 01:00:44.599
We choose to set out on adventures,

01:00:45.350 --> 01:00:47.018
despite knowing the dangers.

01:00:58.863 --> 01:01:00.948
Hop on. It's dangerous here at night.

01:01:02.617 --> 01:01:03.826
You know I won't get on.

01:01:07.080 --> 01:01:10.083
Take care. Thanks for everything.

01:01:12.085 --> 01:01:13.628
Are you really going to end this?

01:01:18.132 --> 01:01:22.387
Ms. Seo Mi-rae, would you like
to part ways with Gu Yeong-il?

01:01:28.893 --> 01:01:30.978
You'll manage fine, right?
Your relationship.

01:01:33.523 --> 01:01:36.693
Just follow your heart.
Be brave even when you're afraid.

01:01:38.444 --> 01:01:39.529
I know that too.

01:01:41.197 --> 01:01:42.990
I remember when you were clueless.

01:01:45.785 --> 01:01:46.786
Bye now.

01:02:07.640 --> 01:02:10.143
YES

01:02:15.064 --> 01:02:15.898
Kyeong-nam!

01:02:18.818 --> 01:02:20.528
You're running again. I told you not to.

01:02:23.114 --> 01:02:23.948
It's dangerous.

01:02:24.031 --> 01:02:26.242
Relationships are dangerous.

01:02:29.495 --> 01:02:31.622
Love is even more dangerous.

01:02:36.252 --> 01:02:38.588
If you head out earlier,
you won't have to run.

01:02:39.422 --> 01:02:40.757
You and your nagging.

01:02:52.894 --> 01:02:55.897
But this time, I think I'll be okay.

01:02:57.356 --> 01:02:58.441
Because it's us.

01:06:07.880 --> 01:06:12.885
Subtitle translation by: Daham Yoon
